{
  "texts": [
    "Despite the power of Large Language Models (LLMs), even with the provision of some examples, these models struggle with more complex tasks.",
    "Notably, reasoning problems, such as arithmetic or commonsense reasoning, are recognized as challenging (WOLFE, 2023).",
    "In order to enhance the language models' ability to perform such tasks, Wei et al. (2023) introduced the Chain of Thought (CoT) technique.",
    "This approach involves inserting several example solutions into the LLM's prompt (as in Section 3.2.3.2) and breaking down the complex problem into intermediate steps.",
    "It provides a logical sequence of reasoning to guide models in generating more precise and coherent responses."
  ]
}